AZ CLI —> Azure Command line interface
——————————————————————
What is the diff between/w “imperative way and Declarative way”

az login
az account show
az account set —subscription (id/Name)
az group create -l (location) -n (Rg-name)
az group delete -n (Rg-Name)
az group list —output=table
————————————————————————
az appservice plan create -g (rgname) -l (location) -n (Name of the Appservice plan)
az appservice plan update -n (Name of the Appservice plan) —sku (Plan-Name) #{F1, B1}
az appservice plan delete -n (Name of the Appservice plan)
az appservice list -output=table
———————————————————————
az webapp create -g (RG-Name) -p (Plan_Name) -n (Name of the AP-svc-name)
az webapp delete -g (RG-Name) -n (Name0ftheWebAPP)
az webapp list —output=table
————————————————————————
az storage account create -g (RG-Name) -n (Name) -l (location) —sku (LRS-Names) {standed_LRS}
az storage container create -n (Name of the Conatiner) —account-name (SA-Name){any anme}
az storage container delete -n (Name of the Conatiner) —account-name (SA-Name)
az storage account delete -g (RG-Name) -n (Name)
————————————————————————
az key vault create -g (RG-Name) -l (location) -n (Name)
az keyvault list
az key vault delete -g (RG-Name) -n (Name of our keyvault)
